{
  "stem": "10446.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So it took hours and hours to compose one letter, if you wanted to convey any message.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that's how we communicated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and finally, we could not do anything at all, except wait.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a very difficult time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had some money outside of the country, which happened to be money that we had sent to our representative for business purposes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's what we lived on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I also had smuggled some money to England-- not very much, but just enough to see us through.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "One time-- and it was in 1936-- I still had my passport.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we still had-- we had business connections with England, selling hops.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My father had some money put aside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And unbeknownst to him, I took it out of the safe and put it in my pocket, and took it with me on that trip.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And again, I took a sleeping car to be safe, on the way to Belgium, and then from Belgium by ship to England.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And when we approached the Belgian border, where the French-- the Germans would come and ask questions, I didn't know what to do with the money.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "First, I put it under the rug, in my sleeping compartment.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And then I didn't feel safe, because if it had been found, they would have known where it came from.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So I took it to the toilet.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I lifted up the brush from the container it was in, put it into the water, and put the brush on top.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And that's where it crossed the border.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "After we crossed the border, I took it out again, spread the bills on my bed to dry, and then collected them again and gave them to a friend in England, who kept it, who-- there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that was the money that we lived on while we were waiting for American immigration visas in England.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My French transit visa was expiring.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And our French friends prevailed upon the consulate to extend the visa.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were ready to deport me back into Germany, which would have been the end.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then we had a hearing and they were able to convince the consulate to renew the visa.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Persuasion and I suspect a little money, too, on the side.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never found out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was an absolutely terrible time, a nightmare with nothing to do, and the anxiety of what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "During that time, while we're waiting, the Czechoslovakian crisis broke out, where Hitler invaded Czechoslovakia and war was about to break out then and there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- then there finally was a conference between Hitler and Daladier, the French premier, and Chamberlain, the English chancellor.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they gave into Hitler and gave him Czechoslovakia so he could occupy it peacefully, without going to war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was how war was avoided.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And if war had broken out, at that time it would've been the end of my mother and Hella, and we would never have seen each other again.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At that time, Chamberlain came back to England and waved the document that he had signed with Hitler, and said on the radio, I'm bringing you piece in our time.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was over optimistic.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] Then finally, the brewery was written over to the Nazi party, without any compensation at all.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my mother and Hella got their exit visas.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- I think at that time they called us and told us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then they told us they were going to be in Strasbourg, by train-- flying was not very well developed in those days-- and at a certain hour.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father and I were at the platform in Strasbourg.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the train pulled in and the two women were not there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were absolutely desperate and didn't know what to do-- no way of getting in touch with them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we decided to wait several hours, until the next train was due.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And on that train, they came.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Did Hella tell you what happ--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It turned out that at the border station in Kehl they were, as Jews, taken off to train to be sure that they had no valuables on them, no real jewelry.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All our jewelry had to be surrendered to the Nazi party.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It so happened that a Jewish woman, who was ahead of them, was decorated with costume jewelry from top to bottom.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she had to be examined carefully to be sure that there was no genuine jewelry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's what took so long that they missed the train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then they took the next one.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then we were finally reunited.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We decided to get away from-- as far away from Germany as possible.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
